Refit model 2 with informative prior for bayes factor.

Time to figure out a prior for that interaction.We know, the hypothesis predicts a positive interaction, and it should nearly eliminate the lexical overlap effect at 3 years old. The mean priming lexical boost is 1.4, so lets assume that the priming effect increases linearly by .45 a year. The regression coefficient for the 3way interaction is then

logit_prior2= c(prior(normal(0,2), class=sd), 
                 prior(normal(.45, .15), coef="Prime_type:Verb_match:Agec"))
m2b <- brm(Response ~ 1 + Prime_type*Verb_match*Agec + (1 + Prime_type*Verb_match|| Case_ID) + (1 + Prime_type*Verb_match*Agec || Trial_verb), logit_prior2, family="bernoulli", iter=30000, cores=4, save_all_pars=TRUE, sample_prior="yes", data=XSectional)
